More than 550 dead on Beijing roads in first eight months of 1996 
Beijing road accidents in the first eight months of the year claimed
551 lives, the figure earlier expected for all of 1996, press reports
said Wednesday.
Police cautioned 1.74 million drivers and arrested 155 people and
courts later withdrew the licences for 260 drivers, according to the
China Business Weekly.
The newspaper highlighted the growing number of drivers trying to flee
after accidents. It said there were 237 cases between January and
August. Beijing courts sentenced eight of the drivers to jail terms of
between 18 months and six years.
There were 70,000 deaths in traffic accidents nationwide in China in
1995, 7.7 percent more than in 1994.
